data.title: Soldier Named 'Ace of Syria'
data.meta_description: U.S. Army Gen. Michael Kurilla, commander of the U.S. Central Command, presents an Army Achievement Medal with “C” Device to Spc. Dylan A. Green, a forward area air defense and nighthawk operator with Combined Special Operations Joint Task Force – Levant, on Dec. 14, 2023 in northeastern Syria. Green was awarded the ARCAM for his service as a forward area air defense and nighthawk operator and shooting down six drones. (Photo by U.S. Army Reserve Jeffrey Daniel and caption by U.S. Army Reserve Sgt. Emma Scearce)
